SIMPLE: incrassated
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incrassated
<hw>In*cras"sa*ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>incrassatus</ets>, p.
p.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Made thick or thicker; thickened;
inspissated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Thickened; becoming thicker.</def>
<rj><au>Martyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Swelled out on some particular
part, as the antenn⟦ae⟧ of certain insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incrassation</ent>⟦br⟧
